communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The causative agent, according to the current report, is serotype 4. Since the start of the epizootic in Romania, reportedly on 24 Aug 2014, 85 outbreaks have been reported in 6 provinces; an administrative map of Romania is available at http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:ROMANIA_judete.jpg.

BTV-4 was apparently earlier reported to be rapidly spreading this summer [2014] in Greece, Bulgaria and the former Yugoslavian republic (FYR) of Macedonia. The latter 2 countries submitted on 1 Sep 2014 their respective follow-up reports to the OIE, including interactive maps showing the new foci. The reports are available at:

FYR Macedonia: http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=15913;

Bulgaria: http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=15880.

The updated total outbreaks per species in the 4 countries since their respective dates of start are as follows:

Greece (last updated 6 Aug 2014)
